&lt;p&gt;Therefore resultant magnetic field,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\mathrm{B}=\sqrt{\mathrm{B}_{1}^{2}+\mathrm{B}_{2}^{2}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And symmetrical &amp;rArr; B&lt;sub&gt;1&lt;/sub&gt; = B&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;there4;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(B_{1}=\sqrt{2} B=\sqrt{2} \frac{\mu_{0} I}{2 r}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(B_{1}=\frac{\mu_{0} I}{\sqrt{2 r}}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The net magnetic field is directed at angle of 45&amp;deg; with either of the fields.&lt;/p&gt;

